tweet: I remain committed to working with the many groups, like @PPFA, that are on the frontlines fighting HIV/AIDS. And, I will continue my work to spread awareness and advocate for funding for HIV/AIDS treatment and prevention programs.

Since I was first elected to public office in 1983, I have fought to address HIV/AIDS at home and abroad. Let us continue to get informed and educate one another about the risks, and work against the stigma associated with HIV/AIDS.
I was proud to join @DrLeanaWen and @PPFA to observe #WorldAIDSDay. We remember those who we have lost to HIV/AIDS and honor their memory by recommitting to this fight. pic.twitter.com/lc1NKT1RQl

My bill — the CARE Act — would provide stable, long-term funding for states and local communities to address the #opioid crisis.

These sobering numbers highlight the devastating effects of the #opioid public health crisis. #Opioids kill 134 people a day, but only 1 in 10 people with addiction are getting treatment.
